{{User:所有盒子/沙盒32/11}}[[Category:International Second Dimension Organization]][[Category:Groups]]{{DISPLAYTITLE: International Second Dimension Organization}}<br><br><br>
<div style="border: 30px solid #fff;">
<big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><b><center>About us</center></b></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></div>
<div style="border: 60px solid #fff;">
<center><big><big><big>One place where the world's nations comes together to study <span style="color:#40b8e8;">an alternate world that humanity has never imagined</span>.</big></big></big></center></div>

<div style="border: 30px solid #fff;">
The International Second Dimension Organization is a United Nations agency established in 1987, which facilitates cooperation among 122 nations around the world to explore the unknown.

The second dimension is an unknown and dangerous place for humanity, and the public is not yet ready to understand it. Since its establishment, we have been focusing on the human rights issues of supernatural creatures in the second dimension, dealing with supernatural threats, the rational utilization of supernatural objects, and the peaceful development of the second dimension by various countries. With the advancement of technology, humanity is adapting at an astonishing rate to things that cannot be explained by science. In the near future, the second dimension will become a new homeland suitable for human habitation.</div>

<div style="background: #F5F5F5; display: inline-block; font-family: Sofia Sans; color: #1e4b76; text-align: left; border: 10px solid #fff;width:100%">
<div style="border: 30px solid #F5F5F5;width:100%">
<br><br><big><big><big><big><big><b>Our Emblem</b></big></big></big></big></big><br>
Do you know that the emblem of the International Second Dimension Organizationwas designed by a group of Chinese designers? It was officially approved through Confidential Resolution No. 122 (II) at the ISDO Conference on February 1st, 1988. This symbolizes that the emblem has become the official emblem of ISDO and has since been used in all aspects related to ISDO. This emblem is modified from the emblem of the United Nations. The olive branches on both sides symbolize the peaceful development of the second dimension, while the infinity symbol in the middle not only represents the infinite space of the second dimension but also implies humanity's boundless curiosity about the unknown. It has practical applications and can be used to identify ISDO to all relevant parties in the conflict areas of the second dimension.<br><br>
</div></div>

<div style="border: 170px solid #fff;"><center>
<big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><b>SDT</b></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big><center><div style="border: 3px solid #009edb;width:75%"></div></center><br>
[[File:treatyI.png|class=fit-image|link=]]<br><br>In 1987, 12 nations engaged in the research of the second dimension signed the Second Dimension Treaty. Today, the number of contracting parties to this treaty has reached 122 nations.<br><br><b><u>Full text</u> <span style="color:#40b8e8;">>></span></b></center></div>

<div style="border: 30px solid #fff;">
In 1987, the Second Dimension Treaty (SDT) was signed in Washington, D.C., United States, by 12 founding nations including the United States, the United Kingdom, and the Soviet Union. The treaty entered into force the following year and has since been acceded to by multiple countries, with the current number of contracting parties reaching 122. The treaty contains critical provisions governing the rational development of the second dimension, such as the second dimension may only be used for peaceful purposes(Article I). Serving as a key basis for ISDO's activities in the second dimension, this treaty remains a pivotal document in shaping the progress of its exploration. To advance its objectives and ensure compliance with treaty provisions, Article 7 mandates that all areas of the second dimension, including all stations, installations, and equipment within these areas, shall be open for inspection at all times(Article VII).</div>

<div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-around; background-color: #F3F3F3; padding: 10px;">
<div style="width: 48%; background-color: #F3F3F3; padding: 20px; text-align: left;">
<big><big><big><big>'''Inside'''</big></big></big></big><div style="border: 1px solid #009edb;width:25%"></div>
<br><br>Inside the second dimension, forces of ISDO are always ready to explore uncharted spaces, engage in battles with supernatural entities, rescue those who are trapped, maintain peace, and put an end to conflicts.<br><br>
</div>
<div style="width: 48%; background-color: #F3F3F3; padding: 20px; text-align: left;">
<big><big><big><big>'''Outside'''</big></big></big></big><div style="border: 1px solid #009edb;width:25%"></div>
<br><br>Outside of the Second Dimension, ISDO focuses on occult research, and with our help, the Second Dimension research institutes in various countries are running in an orderly manner.
</div>
</div>
<br><br><br><br><br>

<center>
<div style="background: #009edb; display: flex; justify-content: space-around; font-family: Sofia Sans; color: white; text-align: left; border: 10px solid #fff;width:85%">
<div style="width: 38%; background-color: #009edb; padding: 20px; text-align: left;"><br><br><br>
<center><big><big><big><big><big><big>'''Members'''</big></big></big></big></big></big></center><br><br><br>
</div>
<div style="width: 58%; background-color: #009edb; padding: 20px; text-align: left;">
<br>{{Collapse|num=2|initial=[[File:nationsI.png|class=fit-image|link=]]|final=<br>Since its establishment, ISDO has grown from 12 members to 122 today. All members have the same rights, and everything they say carries the same weight in ISDO.<br><br>
|body=}}
</div>
</div></center>

<br><br><br><br><br>

